<h1>VoiceLeader: Home</h1>
<p>VoiceLeader is a nifty little tool for error checking (and eventually, creating) simple four 
   part voice-leading exercises.  By supplying the program with sequences of notes (in Soprano, 
   Alto, Tenor, and Bass), you can check for specific voice leading errors, 
   and print out a roman numeral analysis for the exercise.</p>
 
<hr>
 
<h2>Submit Your Music</h2>
<form id="form" action="/results" method="POST">
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Key</legend>
    <select name="key">
    <option value="sharp 0">C Major / a minor</option>
    <option value="sharp 7">G Major / e minor</option>
    <option value="sharp 2">D Major / b minor</option>
    <option value="sharp 9">A Major / f# minor</option>
    <option value="sharp 4">E Major / c# minor</option>
    <option value="sharp 11">B Major / g# minor</option>
    <option value="sharp 6">F# Major / d# minor</option>
    <option value="sharp 1">C# Major / a# minor</option>
    <option value="flat 5">F Major / d minor</option>
    <option value="flat 10">Bb Major / g minor</option>
    <option value="flat 3">Eb Major / c minor</option>
    <option value="flat 8">Ab Major / f minor</option>
    <option value="flat 1">Db Major / b-flat minor</option>
    <option value="flat 6">Gb Major / e-flat minor</option>
    <option value="flat 11">Cb Major / a-flat minor</option>
    </select>
  </fieldset>
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Notes</legend>
